korean:
  title: 산장 우야
  author: 고조기
  language: kor
  text: |-
    어젯밤 송당에 비 내리어
    시냇물 소리 베개 서쪽이 울리더니
    먼동 트자 뜰 앞의 나무를 보니
    숙조는 아직도 가지를 뜨지 않았네
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0220_010_0090&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Rain Night at the Mountain Lodge
  author: Ko Cho-ki
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Last night rain fell upon the pine hall,
    the creek's voice echoing through my western pillow.
    At dawn's first light, I gazed upon the courtyard trees—
    the roosting birds had not yet left their branches.
  footnotes:
    - The 'western pillow' suggests the poet's sleeping position aligned toward the west, with the creek sounds resonating from that direction.
    - The distinction between 'dawn's first light' (먼동 트자) and the birds' reluctance to depart emphasizes a moment of quiet transition between night and day.
